Installation Instructions
=========================

----------------
 Debian package
----------------

if you use debian, ubuntu, or some other similar distribution,
install pysum using the *.deb package (available on the project page
https://developer.berlios.de/project/showfiles.php?group_id=9993)

1.- Download your chosen .deb package via wget or another method

2.- From the terminal type sudo dpkg -i packagename.deb
    (replacing packagename with the name of the package)

Note: You can install *.deb file using a gui (graphical interface).
For example Gdebi installed and does the work for you. It even checks
if any dependencies are missing!


----------------
 Manual install
----------------

== Depends ==

pysum depends on the Python runtime and associated libraries.

Python (>= 2.5) : http://www.python.org
PyGTK (>= 2.8) : http://www.pygtk.org

== Run Source code (without installing) ==

You can find the source code of pysum in /src. To run (without
installing), in a terminal use the following syntax:

$ cd src
$ python pysum.py

== Install (manually)==

Copy the files in /src and /img directory to any other directory you
like (for example in your home, in /usr/share, etc.)


Note 1:
-------
To work the pysum.glade file must be in the same directory as
pysum.py OR ELSE you have to edit the value of RESOURCES_DIR
specifying the location of the directory in where the pysum.glade
file is found (aprox. lines 22-30 in /src/pysum.py), defaut value is
RESOURCES_DIR = "/usr/share/pysum"

Note 2:
-------
The images and icons for the program (pysum.png, pysum.svg,...) must
be in the /img directory or in the same directory as pysum.py

For example if you put the script in: /home/user/foo/pysum.py and the
program needs open the image pysum.png, the program will try to open
the image in the following locations (in order):
1)  /home/user/foo/img/pysum.png
2)  /home/user/foo/pysum.png
3)  /home/user/img/pysum.png
4)  IMG_DIR value (aprox. lines 22-30 in src/pysum.py)

If you need to establish a different location, please edit the value
of IMG_DIR specifying the location of the directory (aprox. lines 
22-30 in src/pysum.py), defaut value is IMG_DIR = "/usr/share/pysum"


--------------
 Translations
--------------

Check the README file in the /po directory for instructions.
